entries.femaleVariant: Johnny's currently indisposed.
You come alone.
Johnny's currently indisposed.
You truly believe time to be your greatest concern?
Hello, Alt.
Place ever look the same?
This place... changes every time. Feels like I'm... deeper.
Wasting time talking. Let's just do this.
Program – how do I use it?
You exist or you do not exist. Two states of being separated by death.
Say what you want, but I rose from the dead.
Matter of perspective. Think what you will, but it seems to me I rose from the dead. Only question is – what now?
entries.maleVariant: Matter of perspective. Think what you will, but seems to me I rose from the dead. Only question is – what now?

entries.femaleVariant: You believe you cheated death?
It is death that has cheated you.
You are in between.
Need your help, Alt. Don't got a lotta time left.
Can't tell if that's a good or bad thing.
Your perception of cyberspace – that is what changes.
You adapt to it – the raw flow of data. It follows that your world gradually fades.
Sayin' the more I'm here the more I lose touch with the outside, with reality?
He is buried deeper. You treat him like an unwanted passenger – a backseat dreamer of a world not his own.
Had no choice.
Thought you didn't care a lick about Johnny anymore.
Had no choice. It was the only way I could come here, meet with you.
Seemed to me you didn't care a lick about Johnny.
That he ceased to exist for you, even.
If he did not exist, you and I would have nothing to discuss.
Repression. You are good at this and improving.
Is that so? Didn't you cheat death?
Speak for yourself. Didn't you cheat death?
Is this what you believe?
Your code, your consciousness… AIs live beyond reality's boundary, they live forever.
But we are not immortal.
No time to lose. I'm ready.
Integrated? So that's why you want to get into Mikoshi.
It opens a secure connection.
There. I sent a program to your netrunner's shard. Once inside Mikoshi, use it.
Need to find a specific access point?
What's the program do? Is it dirty?
What's on the shard? A vectored virus?
A back door.
It will open a passage for me. This is how you will get me into Mikoshi. Only then will I be able to help you.
Hope you haven't cooked up any surprises, Alt.
Use the key once you have reached Mikoshi.
What'm I supposed to do with the shard?
You must slot it into an access point. I will take care of the rest.
This meeting will not be our last – should you succeed.
Should I look for a specific access point? Can already tell you ICE all the way to Tokyo'll be backing every single one.
Some need but a barely cracked door to enter. Use the shard in Mikoshi. Leave the security to me.
Until then.
What should I expect there – in Mikoshi?
A boundary to cross. In all likelihood, the sole moment of your life when you feel the true weight of your existence.
A burden for which you cannot prepare.
Oh, why don't you swoop down on your chariot and enlighten me? Surely an all-powerful AI can handle that.
entries.maleVariant: Why don't you swoop down on your chariot and enlighten me? Surely an all-powerful AI can handle that.

entries.femaleVariant: Your logic is flawed. You seek simple answers where there simply are none. This is the very illusion upon which your world is based.
Your perception will shatter into billions of strings of unfiltered data.
You lose nothing. Cyberspace is where we awake from what we know as dreams.
You witness your mind's defense systems slowly give in.
Lemme get this straight. Johnny's your reason for helpin' me?
Sorry, didn't come here to gab about Johnny.
Lemme get this straight. Mean to say you only agreed to help me 'cause of Johnny?
And since he's not here this one time, you're thinkin' of backin' out?
I do not aim to back out. I have my own intentions for Mikoshi.
Hmm, 'cause for a second you were displeased and I seemed a side note to all this.
To observe the two of you interacting... informative.
Don't got much time left.
Nope, sorry, did not come here to gab about Johnny.
This all just an experiment to you? Are we just fresh data to analyze, do what you want with?
All this, everything – just an experiment to you?
Don't got much time left.
You were actually out to prove him wrong, weren't you?
Damn shame, really. You were out to prove him wrong, here, in person. But all you got is me.
Think there's still some old Alt Cunningham left in you after all.
That Johnny is absent proves that I have won it.
This is not an experiment. It is a debate.
Prefer to just talk to him?
Would you rather just talk to him?
Discussion with any isolated construct is pointless. I can simply read it like any other segment of code.
Yeah, seen how you and Johnny like to... debate.
Johnny also imagined he had more in common with you than with me.
Do you recall when he referred to you as the "human factor?" He thought of himself, too.
That Soulkiller had not changed him, that he, too, remains a "human factor."
And that is why he thought he could shape your will.
Now, absented and imprisoned, he understands what he is – a cluster of data.
Imagining his personality, his character strong enough to shape your will.
Nah, Johnny's made his peace with my decision.
Of course. He had no choice. He understands this now.
The sole "human factor" here is you.
Yeah, well, said human factor's rapidly runnin' outta time.
You will begin to understand, but only in Mikoshi.
Currently...
What should I expect?
Enlighten me right here and now – why not.
At this moment, you would accept any answer if it made you feel better.
Hm. Guess that'd be... human of me?
Such classifications no longer apply in Mikoshi.
But I'll make it through.
Johnny – what about him?
And Johnny? What happens to him?
I lack the data required to answer this question.
I'll make it through.
Constructs imprisoned there – gonna set them free?
While Mikoshi will not.
There anything we can know for certain?
Yes. That Mikoshi will be no more.
They will be integrated with me.
Not sure Johnny'd like the sound of that.
Constructs'll be "integrated?" Mean you're gonna absorb 'em. Assimilate.
No wonder you jumped at this chance. You wanna destroy Mikoshi, swallow all the psyches in there.
Mikoshi is a prison.
Not sure Johnny'd like the sound of that.
And yet he is absent because you feel you must make the decision.
It is the same situation in form.
Huh, hardly. Doubt you'll first gab with those constructs, ask 'em what they think.
There would be no point in this.
Through me, they gain the chance to become part of something greater.
Hey, Alt.
V?
You say nothing. Why?
